programme.desc: Bladesmiths and survivalists tests their weapons through a knife course. Can a Yatagan Sabre hybrid survive the course? Will one of the female blade wielders accomplish a Knife or Death first?

programme.desc: Adam feels a 1956 Chevrolet Bel Air station wagon with a supercharged motor is fit for his client. Mobsteel readies itself for the majestic inauguration of its downtown Detroit shop.

programme.title: Pawn Stars S20E527
programme.desc: An 18th century sea map from the legendary Captain Cook has Rick exploring a big deal. Will he get this sale or face stormy waters?

programme.title: Storage Wars S11E242 !
programme.desc: Back in Torrance, Mary dabbles with Dave's dark arts; Kenny takes some excavation lessons; Brandi and Jarrod quit horsing around long enough to stumble across a wartime bad habit.

programme.title: Storage Wars S11E240
programme.desc: In Stanton, Dave finds that sometimes making a profit is like pulling teeth; Mary grinds to get into the black; Ivy's locker ends up sucking and blowing.

programme.title: North Korea: Dark Secrets
programme.desc: This two-hour special reveals the complicated history, extreme politics and rigid societal standards that have created a legacy of internal oppression and external aggression.

programme.title: History Drama: Six S2E7
programme.desc: A firefight breaks out in a remote village where the Navy SEALs are hiding. Out of options, Gina makes a decision that will completely change the mission's course.

programme.title: The Pickers S13E31
programme.sub-title: Best Of: Don't Mess With Texas
programme.desc: Mike and Frank head to the Lone Star State to see if everything is bigger in Texas.

programme.title: Wild Congo E2
programme.desc: Our closest relatives can be found hidden deep inside the dense jungles that surround the Congo and its feeding rivers, with three of the world's four species of great apes living in the Congo Basin. With Bonobos that use sex as a solution to conflicts and fish with long noses or gigantic trunks, the Congo has become a test laboratory of evolution and an El Dorado of biodiversity.

programme.title: Thailand's Wild Side E1
programme.desc: Across Thailand's myriad landscapes, animals face a constant challenge - to find food. From misty rainforests to rich wetlands, salty mangrove forests to busy cities, they're locked in a deadly battle either to search out their prey or avoid becoming someone else's dinner. Their survival depends on their wits, guile and ingenuity, and losers pay the ultimate price. It's all to play for.

programme.title: Thailand's Wild Side E2
programme.desc: In the Mating Game, creatures are pushed to the limits in the pursuit of a perfect partner and the challenge of raising a family.

programme.title: Japan's Wild Year
programme.desc: Japan is synonymous with crowded high tech cities. In fact around three-quarters of Japan is uninhabited forests, mountains and coast lines. Here a great diversity of wildlife ekes out an existence adapted to a country with great extremes of climate. From the tropics in the south to the sub-arctic climate of Hokkaido island. From the northernmost primates in the world, the snow monkeys, bears, giant hornets and the weird goat-antelope serow, to the iconic red-headed crane and the abundant cherry salmon, the life blood of Japanese rivers.

programme.title: Jane
programme.desc: Using a trove of never-before-seen footage, the film tells the story of Jane's early explorations and research in Tanzania, focusing on her groundbreaking field work, her relationship with her cameraman and husband Hugo van Lawick, and the chimpanzees that were the subject of her study.

programme.title: Before The Flood
programme.desc: Before the Flood captures a three-year personal journey alongside Academy Award-winning actor Leonardo DiCaprio as he interviews individuals from every facet of society around the world, including his discussions on climate change with President Obama and Pope Francis, to provide pragmatic views on what must be done today and in the future to prevent catastrophic disruption of life on our planet.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

programme.title: Iran's Wild Side
programme.desc: Iran's Wild Side offers a rare look into Iran's wondrous wildlife and nature. This documentary features the marvels of this little-known land, nested in the Middle East. From the hot arid deserts and their shifting sands, to the breath-taking snow-capped mountains and their unique inhabitants, and to the lush greenery of mangroves and their unusual creatures, Iran is a land cloaked in mystery and extremes.

programme.title: Africa's Wild Side: Dynasties
programme.desc: Botswana is home to exotic and diverse creatures, but all share one single purpose: keep the bloodline alive. From finding a mate, to raising the next generation, Africa's most beloved animals fight for survival every day.

programme.title: Access 360 World Heritage S2E7
programme.desc: The famed Galapagos Islands teem with fantastic wildlife. The animals that could survive the long journey and harsh climate thrived in an isolated sanctuary. But that isolation left them vulnerable to the threats of the outside world. Now the islands' guardians reveal the hidden patterns of these endangered creatures with latest technology, and gain the critical insights needed to save them.

programme.title: Photo Ark: Rarest Creatures
programme.desc: Join National Geographic photographer Joel Sartore as he travels to Madagascar, China, the Czech Republic, and New Zealand, to photograph creatures found nowhere else on the planet, and add them to his Photo Ark.

programme.title: Jane Goodall: The Hope
programme.desc: Dr, Jane Goodall arrived at a 1986 conference as a scientist and-after learning the extent of the threat facing chimpanzees-left as an activist. The film begins with this critical transformation and follows Jane through three decades of advocacy work. Jane knew she must take action to protect chimps and other animals living in the wild, to improve the well being of chimps in captivity and to inspire a young generation of change makers for this vital work to continue. In a moment in which the environmental crisis can seem overwhelming, Jane has made it her mission to encourage us all that solutions are within reach. Our cameras capture Jane as she travels over 300 days a year, meeting with everyone from schoolchildren in Zanzibar to Silicon Valley tech giants to Prince Harry, using wisdom, heart and humor to spread a message of hope and show that every individual has the potential be a catalyst and create lasting change.

programme.title: Wild Korea E2
programme.desc: The notorious demilitarized zone of Korea has existed on the boundary of two warring nations for nearly 70 years where a tense standoff still remains. However, amidst the barbed wire fences and thousands of land mines, a unique natural wonderland from wild boar to giant hornets to rare cranes peacefully co-exist alongside the ashes of war.

programme.title: Car SOS S5E4
programme.desc: Oil worker Steve has owned his Aston Martin DB6 for over 20 years. After buying it for a bargain price the car became his pride and joy but when it broke down his attempts to repair the Aston failed. Since then a serious fall and chronic health problems have taken their toll and restoring the British classic is now out of his reach. While Fuzz struggles with an engine that hasn't turned over in 20 years Tim will have to do his best to get all the right Aston parts which are notoriously expensive.

programme.title: China Relics Decoded E5
programme.desc: China has built some of the most impressive structures that have lasted the test of time, such as the Forbidden City and the Great Wall of China. But as the nation modernizes, so do its architectural needs and aspirations. Historian Sam Willis explores the history of Chinese architecture, the innovations and cultural considerations involved, and how it has evolved for the growing cities and future generations.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E8
programme.desc: With the small quota running out and top Southern Captain Greg Mayer of the Fishin Frenzy sidelined with injury, Northern and Southern fleets see an opportunity to take the lead. Frenzys mates Billon and Dirty are at the helm of the ship and a battle begins between the rookies and veteran captains for the top-earning spot but first the Bluefin have to bite.

programme.title: Seconds From Disaster Compilation E1
programme.desc: Swiss Air 111 fell from the sky due to microscopic fault in the wiring that sparked a fire in the cockpit. This fire grew uncontrollably and led to the demise of 229 people onboard. JAL123 mysteriously crashed just after takeoff into a remote mountainside. Through thorough investigation, it's learned that wear and tear on small repairs cased the untimely death of the 520 people on board.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E5
programme.desc: Hitler's final throw of the dice to win World War Two - a surprise, winter attack against the Allies least defended front line - the Ardennes. Spearheaded by SS Panzer Tiger tanks, the Germans try to cut the Allied forces in two and destroy them. The Germans ruthless advance results in the worst war crimes ever committed against Americans. On both sides, thousands are killed but for the Americans, it's the bloodiest battle of the entire war.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E5
programme.desc: Gok Wan sets foot in the country of romance and elegance in this episode. Renowned for its “haute-cuisine”, Paris possesses the essence of world gastronomy. Gok savors the dishes in rustic country-style and admires the fusion of elegance, beauty and simplicity. Also, Gok explores Chinese food in the region, like Ho Fun and rice porridge.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E13
programme.desc: There's only forty-eight hours left in the Outer Banks Bluefin season, and while a Southern boat leads the fleet, one Northern vessel continues their assault for the top earning spot. With final paychecks on the line, big fish on the hook and so little time, a fight to the finish is the only guarantee.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E1
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when driving on black ice, using food blenders and attempting to bounce off giant inflatables.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E2
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when driving tracked vehicles, jumping down stairs on unicycles and getting into kayaks.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E3
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when driving through snow and cycling around velodromes, and the terrifying effect of a malfunctioning powerline.

programme.title: Science of Stupid S7E4
programme.desc: In this episode we learn the science behind the fails, when attempting a BMX 720 stunt, having fun on playground spinners and trying to parallel park.

programme.title: Street Genius S1E1
programme.desc: In Street Genius, Tim Shaw conducts a series of experiments that involve science, physics and engineering, all of which will blow your mind. Sick of spending time at the car wash? Tim thinks he can get the job done in just 1 second. Want to know how to get a free meal at a restaurant? Watch and find out. Learn how to prevent cash from burning, what the most powerful vegetable is and more!

programme.title: Street Genius S1E2
programme.desc: Tim Shaw takes science to the streets again with a new set of tricks and experiments. Have you ever seen a coffee creamer bomb? Tim teaches viewers the science behind what makes coffee creamer so flammable. Learn how to break your buddy's beer bottle in one swift hand movement. See what happens when you microwave a light bulb, and more, on Street Genius.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E4
programme.desc: China's vast grasslands are a hard place to survive. Battered by ferocious and unpredictable storms throughout the year, the inhabitants of these grasslands have to be adaptable and tenacious to survive. During the short three-month window of summer, the plains residents have to race against time to raise their young before the onset of autumn and winter begin.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E6
programme.desc: In this final episode of Gok's Chinese Takeaway, Gok Wan returns home to London to discover Westernized version of Cantonese cuisine like Chop Suey, Crispy Duck and Sweet and Sour Pork. Finally, Gok draws on the food and culinary influences from his travels throughout Europe, Asia and Australia in order to create his ultimate celebratory feast of Chinese food from around the world.

programme.title: Nazi Megastructures: America's War E6
programme.desc: Spring 1944. An allied invasion of Hitler's Fortress Europe is inevitable, and under the leadership of distinguished commander Field Marshall Erwin Rommel, the Germans begin a comprehensive programme to turn coastal areas into killing zones. But they still have no idea where and when the invasion will come, and in a fascinating game of cat and mouse, the Allies keep them guessing all the way up to 6th June 1944 - D-Day.

programme.title: Drain The Oceans S2E14
programme.desc: Drain the Oceans unlocks the secrets of how the Japanese Empire rose to power in the Pacific and how it harnessed superior technology turning that devastating firepower against the Allies. It reveals hidden secrets of a catastrophic attack on Australia that gave Japan control of the region and how its extraordinary tactics brought the British Empire to its knees.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E4
programme.desc: The newest member of the community, Amanda's story illustrates how the Lawless Island community welcomes newcomers and guides them into self-sustaining Alaskans.

programme.title: Locked Up Abroad S8E6
programme.desc: On an adventure through Central America, Tom Hart Dyke and Paul Winder are kidnapped and have a $3 million price tag placed on their heads. Nine months and no money later, the pair is released into the jungle but after a couple of days roaming, they get lost. They reluctantly decide to return to their captors for proper directions, although they are warned if they do, their heads will roll.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna: North Vs South S5E9
programme.desc: After four uninspired seasons in the Outer Banks, Captain TJ Ott is out to prove he's a contender. Meanwhile Fishin Frenzy fights for the title without their leader as Captain Greg Mayer nurses an injured arm. In a season where the Northern boats are catching more than ever before, Southern boats continue to fish hard against all odds.

programme.title: Seconds From Disaster Compilation E2
programme.desc: Chinhook HC-2 crashed into a hill on the west side of the Mull of Kintyre in Scotland after taking a group of VIP passengers from Northern Ireland to Fort George. The following day would bring a mysterious crash that remains unsolved. When a US Black Hawk falls on the streets of Mogadishu, all hell breaks loose.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E5
programme.desc: Ralph and his two teams build vehicles out of scrap to take on Shane's Lamborghini Huracan Performante in a timed-lap showdown.

programme.title: The Witch Doctor Will See You Now E1
programme.desc: Author and explorer Piers Gibbon travels to Hong Kong to try to uncover the science and secrets behind traditional Chinese medicine. He is joined by two volunteer patients: a transplant survivor and a biker suffering from chronic back pain as they experience a range of unusual treatments. Their goal is to find a cure to their medical ailments that Western medicine has been unable to provide.

programme.title: Wicked Tuna S7E1
programme.desc: The Gloucester, Massachusetts's bluefin tuna fishing fleet is back for another season with the biggest paydays they've ever seen and the most toxic voyages in Wicked Tuna history. FV-Tuna.Com is determined to reclaim the title of Champion of the fleet. With his returning, trusty crew, Captain Dave Carraro plans to start this season by catching the first fish and not stop until he has brought in more fish and more profit than any other boat. But, he'll have stiff competition this year fishing against the best of the best in New England. All boats are returning: as the second place finisher last season, Pinwheel is on a mission to dethrone the champion; Hot Tuna has a renewed sense of purpose, longing to shatter their lackluster reputation; Hard Merchandise is expanding its family operation with a new crew-member ready to make a profit; Wicked Pissah needs to retain and surpass its successful previous season; and Fish Hawk desperately needs to recover from an embarrassing and u.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E1
programme.desc: In the cold swamps of Georgia, Colbert is facing several months of bitter winter ahead of him. He realizes his window for getting meat is quickly closing and a winter struggling for protein would be excruciating. In a remote spot in southern Utah, Matt returns home to his pit house to discover the land has changed. He needs to check his resources and assess if he’ll have enough to survive through the colder months.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E7
programme.desc: Thorn goes on a nutria hunt hoping to provide protein that Delia and he need to survive, Tony and Amelia take a big step in their homesteading journey and attempt to sell goods at market in town, Colbert is in the midst of a natural disaster as rising waters put his new cabin construction at risk, and Matt goes on a turkey hunt in the canyons he now calls home.

programme.title: Lawless Island Alaska Compilations S2E3
programme.desc: Hans and Timbis story epitomizes what hard work and community can yield. Their decision to build a community garden and willingness to help friends in their time of need, shed light on Lawless Island accomplishments.

programme.title: The Hidden Kingdoms Of China E5
programme.desc: Meet China's most affectionate and vocal monkeys in the remote, seasonal forests of Central China. These mountain forests and all who live here, experience unpredictable and harsh weather in a land that can be covered in snow for 4 months of the year. Follow the journey of a baby Golden snub-nosed monkey during the first year of her life as she learns all about her forest home and battles the elements to survive.

programme.title: The Witch Doctor Will See You Now E2
programme.desc: Piers Gibbon travels to Peru to try to uncover the science and secrets behind traditional shamanic medicine. Joining Piers in the Amazon jungle are Michael Wudyka with constant shoulder and arm pain and asthma suffer Judith Owens, who experience a range of extreme treatments sourced from the jungle itself. Their mission is to cure their own medical ailments that they have struggled to fix at home.

programme.title: Scrapyard Supercar E6
programme.desc: Ralph and his 2 teams of guerrilla mechanics take on Shane's Land Rover Discovery in a daunting hill climb.

programme.title: Facing... E1
programme.desc: Colombian drug lord Pablo Emilio Escobar Gaviria built his cocaine empire on bribes and bodies. Featuring original interviews with the DEA agents, Colombian police officers, drug smugglers, and politicians who hunted and were hunted by Escobar, this episode is equally an intimate portrait and cautionary tale of one man's unchecked megalomania - and his struggle to overcome adversity.

programme.title: Live Free Or Die S3E8
programme.desc: Woodsman Thorn takes Delia on her very first hunt to capture a bird to in an attempt to meld together the wild and domestic sides of his life, homesteaders Tony and Amelia struggle to maintain unruly and destructive pigs, hunter-gatherer Matt invites old friends over for a turkey roast, and frontiersman Colbert enlists the help of two friends to help him finish his cabin in time for spring.

programme.title: Airport Security: Peru E12
programme.desc: On this episode, officers profile a man carrying 20 alpaca skin rugs, who claims that they are souvenirs when they really contain hidden narcotics inside. In another operation, officers inspect the luggage of a young student carrying narcotics in a double-bottom suitcase; they interrogate a hostile passenger who refuses to cooperate with the police; and later on, they spot a suspicious young man carrying almost 3 kilograms of cocaine hidden in his luggage.

programme.title: Gourmet Goes Tribal E19
programme.desc: Food has always been a way to spread joy and happiness for Pablo. When he got a chance to return the favour, Pablo couldn't think of a better way than to cook for the people of North East and share the magic of food with them. Pablo talks about his most innovative dishes given the limited amount of time and unusual ingredients, he churned out some amazing recipes in the North East of India.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E5
programme.desc: Clarke has a good look at one of the most productive harbours in New Zealand. Home to over 20% of the world's seabird biodiversity and with a resident whale population, this unique location is an incredible harbinger of life. Clarke explores some of the harbours hidden features and shows a fishing club that has made big changes to better utilize the ocean around it.

programme.title: Fish Of The Day S3E6
programme.desc: Chasing a Dog Tooth Tuna, Clarke encounters everything but as he tackles the waters off Apia Island, Samoa. Not that he has any complaints as he manages to hook the largest Giant Trevally he has ever captured. programme.title: Island Hunter E3
programme.desc: Easy island vibes, lots of amazing local rum, brilliant natural landscapes and those amazing beaches! Of course, Island Hunter is in Jamaica! But in this episode, host Liesel Hlista shows you a different side of the Irie nation; away from the hordes of people unleashed via cruise liners! She starts off with a quick glimpse and an impromptu jam session at the birthplace of Bob Marley, Trench town, noshes on the most delicious ice cream this side of the hemisphere, and plunges into Mystic mountain's waterfalls. Jamaica is known for being the home of the all-inclusive resort and Liesel finds out exactly why that is - with stays at Ian Fleming inspired Golden eye Hotel as well as Sunset at the Palms! Lazy tubing down the river, limestone foot massages, topped up with historic food tours and experiencing local cuisines such as jerk chicken and the amazing seafood; this is Jamaica, Island Hunter style!

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E8
programme.desc: David explores Kolkata, a city so rich in culture and food tradition. He meets up with Myanck, a local chef from ITC, to check out the city's fish market. programme.desc: Shandong Province is home to China's most famous philosopher- Confucius, Jonathan Clements as a historian and expert on Asian Culture, will be the host of this show. programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E3
programme.desc: First time property developer Cate and her fiancee Nikki are looking to boost their pension pot and they carry out a high risk strategy by pouring all of Cate's life savings into a rundown house they don't even own. Will her dream of making a £200,000 profit turn into a nightmare?

programme.title: Inside T4: Terminal Of Tomorrow
programme.desc: In 2017, Changi Airport served a new high 62 million passengers. By 2030, it plans to bring its capacity to more 150 million passengers. The first step to this expansion is the opening of its new terminal - T4. With the annual world's Best Airport title up for review, Changi is pulling all the stops to elevate the flight experience from the moment a passenger steps into the terminal through the combination of nature, art and technology. From cutting-edge facial recognition technology to 12-metre-tall indoor trees and one the world's largest kinetic sculptures, we reveal how the team behind Changi Airport fuses innovative design and fully automated technological solutions to provide the airport experience Changi is world-renowned for.

programme.title: Easyjet: Inside The Cockpit S1E1
programme.desc: EasyJet, the UK's biggest airline, launched its largest ever pilot recruitment drive including a focus on encouraging more women to apply for this career where females currently make only three per cent of pilots worldwide. Becoming a pilot involves dedication and determination and the trainees come from every walk of life. But does the reality live up to the dream of flying high?

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E2
programme.desc: Michelle and Justin are outdoor enthusiasts and every spare moment is planned around kite surfing and paddle boarding trips. It's time for them to find their very own long beach view.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E2
programme.desc: Clint flies in by sea plane to view the Grizzly Bears up close and also gets his hands dirty at Echo Valley Ranch in British Columbia.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E6
programme.desc: The historic region of Fort Kochi boasts an unexpected blend of cultural influences of Chinese, Indian, Portuguese and British. It also happens to be one of the only places in India where you can eat beef. David goes on a hunt for good stuff, enjoying chili fried and dry-fried beef. He meets up with Chef Ajeeth of the famed Brunton Boatyard to continue the beef-themed adventure at his restaurant.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E7
programme.desc: The beautiful Chinese fishing nets are iconic tourist attractions along the coast of Kochi and David discovers that the fishermen who operate them are just as intriguing. In a true cultural exchange, they teach David how to work the nets while David cooks their catch of the day for them. Later, David visits the idyllic Kayal island retreat where the women workers catch fish using only their hands.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E2
programme.desc: George travels to Cornwall to meet Rebecca and Damian, a young couple who are trading in their house for a debt free life in a cool, luxury American trailer known as a Silver Streak. But with just £10 grand to finish the job can they transform this trailer from trash to vintage treasure?

programme.title: Shandong: Land Of Confucius
programme.desc: Shandong Province is home to China's most famous philosopher- Confucius, Jonathan Clements as a historian and expert on Asian Culture, will be the host of this show. In the course of a whirlwind adventure that spans 9 carefully chosen locations throughout Shandong, Clements, a scholar of modern Asian trends gives us his fascinating take on how China got where it is today.

programme.title: Climbing The Property Ladder E3
programme.desc: First time property developer Cate and her fiancee Nikki are looking to boost their pension pot and they carry out a high risk strategy by pouring all of Cate's life savings into a rundown house they don't even own. Will her dream of making a £200,000 profit turn into a nightmare?

programme.title: Inside T4: Terminal Of Tomorrow
programme.desc: In 2017, Changi Airport served a new high 62 million passengers. By 2030, it plans to bring its capacity to more 150 million passengers. The first step to this expansion is the opening of its new terminal - T4. With the annual world's Best Airport title up for review, Changi is pulling all the stops to elevate the flight experience from the moment a passenger steps into the terminal through the combination of nature, art and technology. From cutting-edge facial recognition technology to 12-metre-tall indoor trees and one the world's largest kinetic sculptures, we reveal how the team behind Changi Airport fuses innovative design and fully automated technological solutions to provide the airport experience Changi is world-renowned for.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E2

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E8
programme.desc: David explores Kolkata, a city so rich in culture and food tradition. He meets up with Myanck, a local chef from ITC, to check out the city's fish market. Later, they head into the kitchen with their fish-market finds and experiment with Kolkata's two signature ingredients: mustard and fresh river fish, and everyone agrees the results are delicious.

programme.title: David Rocco's Dolce India S2E9
programme.desc: The people of Kolkata are so intensely proud of their local cuisine, especially their epic street food. David meets up with Sneha, who takes him on a crazy food tour of the city. They ride the tram and do as the locals do on their quest to sample Kolkata's best street eats, including the famous Kati roll.

programme.title: George Clarke's Amazing Spaces S8E3
programme.desc: The home of the nation's most inventive small spaces continues as George travels to Lancashire to meet Billy, a remarkable 17 year old self-builder who singlehandedly transforms a derelict narrow boat his mum bought for £4000 into a hand crafted floating holiday home for his mum and sister, and the results are amazing.

programme.title: Gok's Chinese Takeaway E1
programme.desc: Gok travels around Barcelona and seeks Western Mediterranean cuisine in this episode. He attempts to make Barcelona sausages with the help of a professional artisan sausage maker. Also, Gok looks for the renowned Chinese restaurant in the territory where peking duck and dim sum are served distinctively in Spanish-style with its original appearance.

programme.title: Food Lab S2E7
programme.desc: Ben arrives at one of his favourite community organisations, Produce to the People, on Tasmania's North-West Coast. He chats to Penelope, the founder of PTTP, and collects some fresh produce from around the farm to use in a recipe. He makes his version of lox and cream with a slight twist and some added pickled vegetables. Dr Mark Turner explains why pickling will preserve your fruit and vegetables.

programme.title: Ariana's Persian Kitchen E7
programme.desc: Ariana drives along the beautiful Caspian Sea in the province of Mazandaran, where she gets to learn all about different varieties of rice grown in nearby rice paddies because of the rich soil and humid climate. Here, she enjoys a big meal in a restaurant with a great view and tastes the famous jam made from citron preserves to sour cherry pickle and many more.

programme.title: Inside Turkish Airlines
programme.desc: This is a 360-degree view of operations for Turkey's biggest airline! They have thousands of travelers to transport, logistical nightmares to overcome, passengers to be intercepted and planes to be fixed. We follow their staff both in the air and on the ground – from pilots and flight attendants to baggage handlers and loadmasters, as they face the challenges of keeping a busy airline running.

programme.title: Easyjet: Inside The Cockpit S1E2
programme.desc: Follow the rookie pilots as they take their first steps from the flight school classroom into the flight simulator, and on to flying large jets with hundreds of passengers on board. This episode, freshly-qualified 20-year-old Ryan Clyde lands for the first time in the dark in Paris with passengers on board - with the added complication that one of them has never flown before, and is extremely nervous. Meanwhile cadet Sophie Trunan learns how to deal with G-forces, and the firm's training captains jet off to France to showcase their skills to seven fledgling pilots.

programme.title: What's For Sale With A View S2E3
programme.desc: Wine enthusiasts Christina and Ed are ready to make their lifelong dream of having a view of a lush green vineyard come true. Their Italian and Chilean roots have led them on a quest to re-locate to wine country.

programme.title: Places We Go S8E3
programme.desc: Clint explores the world famous Rockies as part of the Icefields Parkway including Athabasca Glacier, Lake Louise and Banff.

programme.title: Pond Stars E6
programme.desc: The Pond Stars come out of their shell in Atlanta tackling two wild projects in just five days. Their first job is at an environmental center, creating a pond specifically for rescued turtles as an outdoor classroom for an upcoming kids camp. The second project is to build a 35-foot waterfall and 600-gallon reservoir that will have wildlife flocking to this suburban backyard, for the birds.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S3E5
programme.desc: In a race to beat the big freeze, caribou migrate south to look for mates, but still find time to go head-to-head with their deadly headgear, fighting for rights to the bloodline. In Yellowstone National Park, a badger finds some tasty red fox cubs for brunch but meets their dad, who is willing to fight to the bitter end to protect his babies.

programme.title: Operation Sumatran Rhino
programme.desc: In Borneo, Sumatran rhinos' numbers are down to just single digits, and conservationists are on a desperate mission to save the country's last ones. However, capturing all remaining rhinos in the wild is costly and dangerous. Follow Malaysia's foremost rhino scientists on their incredible quest to breed a future generation and to save this critically endangered species.

programme.title: Lion Kingdom E2
programme.desc: The Glade is a paradise where there is always water, a place where strange things happen. As the dry continues in Ruaha, herds of elephants arrive in the Glade. They dig deep into the sand with their trunks to tap the cleanest waters. The Glade pride copy the elephants - unusual behavior, but not in the Glade. Life carries on in its idiosyncratic way, but soon things may change. Adult male lions are on the horizon, they're following the buffalo. The Njaa pride have already spotted the males. The Njaa are drifters, they consider the buffalo their territory. But even these fearless lionesses will not hunt while the lions are about - and now the males are on their way to the Glade.

programme.title: Killer Animal Tactics
programme.desc: From top predators to clever creatures, these killers are some of the most armed and dangerous animals in the world. In order to survive, they use some of the scariest strategies and lethal weapons like ambush, camouflage, claws and paws, venom, pack hunting and more to take down prey. The name of the game is kill or be killed!

programme.title: Dead By Dawn Compilations E2
programme.desc: Around the world, when the sun goes down, deadly dangers emerge. In the Arabian Desert, a gecko realizes he's not alone when the sand beneath his feet starts shifting. In Southern India, a praying mantis prays as an army of weaver ants march toward his arms and legs. In the African wilderness, a lion cub cries for his mother while a hyena gets closer, and closer. Who will survive the horrors of tonight, and who will be dead by dawn?

programme.title: Operation Sumatran Rhino

However, capturing all remaining rhinos in the wild is costly and dangerous. programme.title: Shark Men S3E11
programme.desc: In the final days of the Cocos Island expedition, the Shark Men are in a race against the clock. To tag the ever elusive hammerheads, the team resorts to midnight fishing and swimming with sharks. And at the moment when teamwork is needed, the team and equipment breaks down. The crane dies and Denny disappears. With only hours to go to implant the crucial tags, will the Shark Men pull through?

programme.title: When Predators Attack (Mashups) E3
programme.desc: Bears are iconic symbols of nature, a treasure to see in the wild?when kept at an appropriate distance. With habitat loss and a changing climate, the world's strongest bears are inching closer to our homes. And nothing beats their killer package. Watch what unfolds when black bears, grizzlies, and giant polar bears face off against prey and people, in a final attempt to stay alive.

programme.title: Cat Attack-Tics
programme.desc: There are 38 species of wild cats on Earth and they live and hunt in almost any terrain. Over millions of years, they have honed their strategy to attack a prey of a specific size. From tree-climbing leopards to skull-crushing Jaguars, from fast-swimming fishing cats to quick-digging sand cats - watch the killer strategies that make wild cats possibly the deadliest family on the planet.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4E5
programme.desc: “Power Struggles' reveals how the most epic battles can be won or lost in a split second. In the world of wild animal fights, nothing is ever certain. We see a female leopard fight a bigger male for her lunch and her life, discover the complex competition amongst the world's largest great apes, and see how a Nile monitor lizard can turn its tail into a show-stopping weapon.

programme.title: The Monster Project E3
programme.desc: Judah Friedlander is in Texas to investigate the myths and legends of one of the most fascinating and elusive beings, the Chupacabra. Its translated name is Goat Sucker, legend says that it drains the blood from its victims leaving behind puncture holes, and that it has the ability to change its colour. So far all sightings have turned out to be coyotes, but is there any truth behind the legend?

programme.title: Monster Fish S5E2
programme.desc: Zeb Hogan hunts for the fresh water Whipray in the Daily River, northern Australia. The largest one caught so far was 10 feet across and weighed around 800 pounds, with a barb over 12 inches long. He then heads to Thailand on the trail of a giant Stingray, reported to be 600 pounds. These rays are said to grow to the size of small trucks. If true, this would be the largest fresh water fish ever.

programme.title: Pond Stars E1
programme.desc: In the season opener, Greg and the crew work to install a giant pond for Tony and Shari, who want a larger home for their koi fish. Meanwhile, a client calls Greg to fix her current pond, but instead of fixing it, Greg transforms the bland backyard into a wild sanctuary. Working on their best to turn two backyards into entirely new ecosystems, the team races to get both projects done.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4E1
programme.desc: From the African Plains to the American Highlands, 'Clash of Titans' exposes nature, red in tooth and claw. Lions go head-to-head, a grey wolf pack takes on a grizzly, hippos hammer out a violent battle, and one of the world's largest monkeys plans a mission to murder. Lust, jealousy, and pure rage fuel deadly encounters in the wild, as the natural world shows its savage side.

programme.title: The Pack E1
programme.desc: A lone lion can hunt, and hunt well, but a pride will take on more and larger prey. We will study the battlefield to understand how a group of individuals develop the tactics and relationships needed and analyze their moves, revealing the nuances of the hunt as it's never been seen before. Discover how lions are pushing the limits of living in a pack.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S5E2 ?
programme.desc: This episode features a dairy goat nursing and protecting a motherless foal. They share hay and drink together every day like a family. A parrot and a boxer cuddle and stay side-by-side without apprehension. These unlikely pals will definitely leave you in sheer amazement.

Then venture into the realm of the smallest of big cats - the Clouded Leopard in the jungles of north east India. Wildlife Cameraman & National Geographic Fellow, Sandesh Kadur is on a mission to uncover their secretive lives.

programme.desc: The relentless pace of work is wearing some of the men down and tensions flare between science and angling teams. Lead scientist Pete Klimley and his second-in-command Alex Hearn clash and come close to an all-out fist fight. At the end of the day, the mission to protect the sharks rises above all else although personality conflicts continue to simmer.

programme.title: Hunter Vs. Hunted E1 !
programme.desc: A Colorado trail runner ends up running for his life, and a peaceful walk in Canadas woods turns deadly. When we enter the realm of wild animals, it can become a case of hunter vs. hunted.

programme.title: Eyewitness Shark Attack: Facing Jaws
programme.desc: As more people bring cameras into the water, they are capturing more shocking footage of the most feared and revered ocean predators-- sharks. With shark attacks on the rise, do these top predators see us as prey? Experts weigh in on some of the most amazing human-shark encounters captured on video to reveal the secrets behind the attacks.

programme.title: Unlikely Animal Friends S5E5
programme.desc: Strong and spiritual bonds forged like long lost soulmates join together in this episode. A tigress and a lioness share an enclosure and play soccer together. Also, a nursery dog buddies up with an Asian goat-antelope. They lean on each other like family and even eat each other's leftovers.

programme.title: Stranger Than Nature: Unhinged E3
programme.desc: Beachgoers are stunned and disturbed when a strange alien-like creature washes up on the shores of Montauk, Long Island. Images posted on the internet show the creature with a bird-like beak, a bald body and what appears to a tag tied to its front limb. Millions of people around the world follow the investigation into just what this creature could be. Could it be a mutant from a top-secret government research lab nearby? In the NamiBrand Reserve in Namibia, millions of circles of bare earth surrounded by lush grass dot the earth for miles in all directions. Known as fairy circles, they are an enduring mystery. What is causing the earth to scorch in these perfect patterns? In Australia, ravenous rodents invade farms in the hundreds of thousands. Farmers and their families throw up their hands in despair choosing death over dealing with the mice. What could be causing the mice, which are not even native to the area, from overrunning farms and livelihoods? When 7% of the world's.

programme.title: Wild Korea E1
programme.desc: Korea is known as a modern, high tech nation; but beyond the bustle of the cities there's a land of stunning natural beauty and remarkable wildlife. There are lush wetlands and mudflats in contrast to the soaring mountains and turbulent seas; and the beautiful goshawk, bottleneck dolphin and curious racoon dog thrive alongside Korea's traditional people as they have for many thousands of years.

Meanwhile, Ed and Greg take a field trip to a nearby high school to construct a courtyard pond to be used as a perfect outdoor classroom.

programme.title: Animal Fight Club S4E2
programme.desc: The plains of Africa are home to nature's most fearsome predators: cheetahs, lions and hyenas. But the battle for survival is never one sided; even the prey can be formidable. We see a mother cheetah come face-to-face with the heavy weaponry of a Grants gazelle, and unpack what happens when three lions make the mistake of their lives and try to take down a pugnacious rhino.

programme.title: Snow Leopard Of Afghanistan
programme.desc: Nat Geo Wild joins the Wildlife Conservation Society (WCS) and an international team of experts, including biologist Boone Smith, to set out on a mission in Afghanistan to find, capture and collar a snow leopard, and release it back into the wild. If they are successful, the expedition can offer a deeper understanding of the rare and beautiful species.

programme.title: Snakes In The City S4E2
programme.desc: Simon and Siouxsie get called to remove an angry black mamba from a huge wood pile. After 5 hours of searching they eventually find it, and it is seriously angry. A vicious spitting cobra spits venom like mad when Simon tries to get it out of a tree cavity, and it takes them almost a month to trap an elusive forest cobra that's been terrorizing trailer park residents!

The Spy: Undercover Operation
programme.desc: Seorang agen yang sedang menyamar di luar negeri berusaha untuk menyeimbangkan pekerjaannya yang rumit dan istrinya yang tak tahu pekerjaannya.

programme.title: Gangster, The Cop, The Devil
programme.desc: Setelah nyaris tewas dari serangan seorang pembunuh berantai nan kejam, seorang bos kriminal bekerjasama dengan seorang detektif setempat untuk menangkap sang pembunuh.

programme.title: Lump Of Sugar
programme.desc: Seorang gadis sangat sedih saat sahabatnya, seekor kuda, dijual. Namun, saat mereka bertemu lagi dua tahun kemudian, keduanya berkesempatan untuk membuat keajaiban dengan bekerjasama dalam sebuah perlombaan.

programme.title: Singles
programme.desc: Tiga sekawan yang menghadapi pasang surut kehidupan mencoba untuk tinggal bersama. Namun, persahabatan mereka diuji kala dua diantara mereka tidur bersama.

programme.title: Running Wild
programme.desc: Seorang pengacara nan kaku bekerjasama dengan seorang detektif pembunuhan yang temperamental dan kejam untuk menangkap seorang bos mafia yang bertanggung jawab atas kematian adik laki-laki seorang jaksa.

programme.title: The Scam
programme.desc: Hyeon-Soo bergabung dengan tim elit yang dibentuk oleh seorang gangster yang menyamar menjadi seorang investor untuk melakukan penipuan terbesar demi mendapatkan 60.000.000 dolar dari pasar saham.

programme.title: Truck
programme.desc: Seorang sopir truk tak sengaja melihat pembunuhan oleh sebuah geng. Ia bersedia membantu membuang mayat-mayat itu agar tetap dibiarkan hidup. Namun, situasi memburuk ketika seorang pembunuh berantai menumpang truknya.

programme.title: Radio Dayz
programme.desc: Sekelompok tim nan unik bersatu untuk membuat siaran langsung drama radio pertama di Joseon saat masa penjajahan Jepang pada tahun 1933.

programme.title: Secret Love
programme.desc: Situasi menjadi semakin rumit saat seorang istri jatuh cinta pada saudara kembar suaminya yang sedang koma.

programme.title: Thread Of Lies
programme.desc: Terpukul akibat bunuh diri sang putri yang berusia 14 tahun, seorang ibu dan putri tertuanya bertekad untuk memecahkan misteri kematian putrinya itu dengan menyelami kehidupan gadis yang merundung sang putri.

programme.title: The Tooth And The Nail
programme.desc: Berdasarkan novel karya Bill S. Ballinger dengan judul yang sama, film ini menceritakan tentang seorang pesulap yang merencanakan trik paling rumit untuk mengungkap konspirasi tersembunyi di balik kematian tunangannya.

programme.title: Gonjiam: Haunted Asylum
programme.desc: Sejumlah orang direkrut untuk menyiarkan langsung pertunjukan horor di Gonjiam, RS paling berhantu di Korea. Untuk menarik lebih banyak penonton, mereka memasang beberapa kejutan seram, tapi keadaan berubah memburuk.

programme.title: RV: Resurrected Victims
programme.desc: Suatu hari, ibu jaksa Jin-hong yang sudah meninggal kembali ke rumah dan mencoba membunuhnya. Ia pun segera menjadi tersangka utama atas pembunuhan ibunya.

programme.title: My Boss, My Teacher
programme.desc: Doo-sik adalah seorang mahasiswa senior di pagi hari dan bekerja di sebuah geng di malam hari. Namun, masalah muncul saat bosnya meminta ia bekerja untuknya di pagi hari, saat ia berada di kampus.

programme.title: Blood And Ties
programme.desc: Seorang jurnalis mencurigai ayahnya adalah seorang penculik kejam yang melarikan diri 15 tahun yang lalu.

programme.title: Along With Gods: Two Worlds
programme.desc: Usai meninggal, pemadam kebakaran Ja-hong dibawa ke alam baka oleh tiga penjaga. Demi bereinkarnasi, ia harus melewati tujuh ujian dalam 49 hari guna membuktikan bahwa ia menjalani kehidupan yang lurus semasa hidup.

programme.title: Along With Gods: Last 49 Days
programme.desc: Tiga malaikat kematian akan memandu jiwa ke-49 mereka, Kim Soo-Hong, ke pengadilan akhirat. Sementara itu, Dewa Penjaga Rumah akan memulihkan ingatan mereka dari 1.000 tahun yang lalu.

programme.title: The Witch: The Subversion
programme.desc: Ja-yoon melarikan diri dari pemerintah dan diadopsi oleh pasangan senior dan kehilangan semua ingatannya. Kemudian, ketika ia muncul di sebuah program TV, orang-orang asing mulai muncul dalam hidupnya.

programme.title: Lost And Found
programme.desc: Ji-ho diam-diam jatuh cinta pada pria yang sama selama 10 tahun terakhir. Saat ia tertabrak mobil sang pria, ia berbohong demi menjadi dekat dengannya, namun justru berakhir dengan bencana.

programme.title: Gangster, The Cop, The Devil

programme.title: Memoir Of A Murderer
programme.desc: Seorang mantan pembunuh berantai dengan penyakit Alzheimer membunuh orang-orang yang telah melakukan dosa 'buruk'. Kini, ia berjuang melindungi putrinya dari pacarnya yang kasar.
